    <img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.mediacurrent.com/sites/default/files/styles/thumb_blog_spotlight/public/draggable-views-01.png?itok=vCkv_R4K" width="200" height="151" alt="Draggable Views" title="Draggable Views" /> <p>When approaching new Drupal projects, I’m always excited to listen and learn about the project’s requirements. It’s an occasion to create just the right solution. With a recent project, I took the opportunity to rethink the use of Nodequeue to manage front page content, and instead used the Draggableviews and Custom Publishing Options projects. Before diving into that solution, let’s step through other solutions to manage front page content, so we can undestand the pros and cons of each.</p>
